{"lemma":"مُحافَظاتُ","slug":"مُحافَظاتُ","root":"ح.ف.ظ","root_slug":"ح-ف-ظ","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ف-ظ","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8499"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B8%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَافَظَ (ḥāfaẓa) (form III)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"preservation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a province; an administrative division of state territory"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"feminine singular of مُحَافَظ (muḥāfaẓ)","tags":["feminine","form-of","singular"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"feminine singular of مُحَافِظ (muḥāfiẓ)","tags":["feminine","form-of","singular"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of حَافَظَ (ḥāfaẓa).\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":["/mu.ħaː.fa.ðˤa/","/mu.ħaː.fi.ðˤa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8499","headword_ar":"مُحَافَظَةٌ","root":"HfZ","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defending"},{"kind":"text","text":"of those persons, or things, that are sacred, or inviolable, or that one is bound to respect or honour, and to defend, (K, TA,) on the occasions of wars; (TA;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HifaAZN","text_ar":"حِفَاظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAfZ Hariymahu","text_ar":"حافظ حَرِيمَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He defended his wife,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wives,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK.) [And hence,] you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu la*uw HifaAZK","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَذُو حِفَاظٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw","text_ar":"ذُو"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHaAfaZapK","text_ar":"مُحَافَظَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is disdainful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scornful."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being mindful, watchful, observant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"regardful:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rEY","text_ar":"رعى"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [see also 5:] or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"keeping, attending,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"applying oneself, constantly, perseveringly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assiduously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) to a thing, or an affair. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAfZ EalaY AlA^amori","text_ar":"حافظ عَلَى الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ElY Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"على الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mHAfZp","text_ar":"محافظة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He kept, attended,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"applied himself, constantly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And hence the saying in the Kur [ii. 239],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAfiZuwA EalaY AlS~alawaAti","text_ar":"حَافِظُوا عَلَى الصَّلَوَاتِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Perform ye the prayers in their proper times:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to Az,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"keep ye, attend ye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apply yourselves, constantly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perseveringly, to the performance of the prayers in their proper times."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HifaAZN","text_ar":"حِفَاظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is also explained as signifying The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being mindful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"observant, of a covenant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"keeping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fulfilling, of a promise, with forgiveness, and holding fast to love"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affection."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}